author: JEFF FIELDER Sports Editor jfielder@starherald.com
title: Hemingford claims Panhandle Conference Volleyball Tourney title
text:
Courtesy photo Hemingford claims Panhandle Conference Volleyball Tourney title 
Members of the Hemingford volleyball team pose for a photo after winning the Panhandle Conference Tournament on Saturday in Edgemont, S.D. Posted: Saturday, October 17, 2015 9:51 pm Hemingford claims Panhandle Conference Volleyball Tourney title JEFF FIELDER Sports Editor jfielder@starherald.com Star Herald 
EDGEMONT, S.D. – The Hemingford volleyball team earned its first Panhandle Conference Tournament championship in years on Saturday at Edgemont, S.D. 
The Bobcats, who received a first-round bye thanks to being the top seed in the tournament, took down Hay Springs 25-9, 25-15 in the semifinal round before toppling Crawford 25-14, 25-20 in the title match.
